He spake no more but still in human form clove a furrow of light through the clouds ; he passes to Luna’s globe, leaves Mercury's threshold and hastens to the gentle airs of Venus, Hence he tra- verses Phoebus’ path, Mars’ baleful fires and J upiter's quiet quartem, and stands upon the very crown of the sky, cold Saturn’s frozen zone. Heaven’s fabric openS, unbidden the shining doors swing back. Bootes prepares a place in the vault of the northern sky, sword-girt Orion unbars the portals of the south 3 they offer welcome to the new star, uncertain each in turn to what region he will betake himself, what constellation he will grace with his presence, or in what quarter he will elect to shine alone.
